%5B%7B%22title%22%3A%22Americans%20are%20exhausting%20their%20excess%20savings%20-%20and%20could%20run%20out%20funds%20this%20quarter%2C%20Fed%20study%20says%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20Person%20Counting%20US%20Dollar%20Bills%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64df4876bd98a6001978e8db%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EMoe%20Zoyari%2FBloomberg%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EAmericans%20are%20burning%20through%20their%20savings%20and%20could%20run%20out%20funds%20as%20early%20as%20this%20quarter%2C%20a%20Fed%20study%20showed.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EAs%20of%20June%2C%20Fed%20estimates%20show%20US%20households%20held%20less%20than%20%24190%20billion%20of%20aggregate%20excess%20savings.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EWith%20excess%20savings%20dwindling%2C%20Americans%20have%20leaned%20on%20their%20credit%20cards%20for%20spending.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAmericans%20are%20exhausting%20their%20pandemic%20savings%20%E2%80%93%20and%20could%20run%20out%20of%20funds%20by%20the%20end%20of%20the%20third%20quarter%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20Bank%20of%20San%20Francisco.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EExcess%20savings%20refer%20to%20the%20difference%20between%20actual%20savings%20and%20the%20pre-recession%20trend%2C%20Fed%20researchers%20said.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20of%20June%2C%20Fed%20estimates%20show%20that%20US%20households%20held%20less%20than%20%24190%20billion%20of%20aggregate%20excess%20savings.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20is%20considerable%20uncertainty%20in%20the%20outlook%2C%20but%20we%20estimate%20that%20these%20excess%20savings%20are%20likely%20to%20be%20depleted%20during%20the%20third%20quarter%20of%202023%2C%26quot%3B%20San%20Francisco%20Fed%20researchers%20Hamza%20Abdelrahman%20and%20Luiz%20Oliveira%20said%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.frbsf.org%2Four-district%2Fabout%2Fsf-fed-blog%2Fexcess-no-more-dwindling-pandemic-savings%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eblog%20on%20Wednesday%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20added%20that%20government%20data%20showed%20consumers%20were%20spending%20beyond%20their%20means%20during%20the%20last%20quarter%20of%202022%20and%20first%20quarter%20of%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Bureau%20of%20Economic%20Analysis%20recently%20revised%20its%20previous%20estimates%20to%20show%20household%20disposable%20income%20was%20lower%20and%20personal%20consumption%20was%20higher%20than%20previously%20reported%20for%20the%20fourth%20quarter%20of%202022%20and%20first%20quarter%20of%202023%2C%26quot%3B%20Abdelrahman%20and%20Oliveira%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20combined%20revisions%20brought%20down%20the%20Bureau's%20measure%20of%20aggregate%20personal%20savings%20by%20more%20than%20%2450%20billion%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20added.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20downbeat%20forecast%20comes%20as%20Americans%20prop%20up%20the%20economy%20through%20their%20strong%20spending%20habits%2C%20helping%20temper%20fears%20that%20the%20US%20could%20slip%20into%20recession.%20But%20dwindling%20savings%20could%20pose%20challenges%20for%20the%20US%20economy%2C%20given%20consumer%20spending%20is%20a%20key%20engine%20of%20growth.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20one%20sign%20of%20falling%20savings%2C%20Americans%20are%20using%20their%20credit%20cards%20more%2C%20racking%20up%20nearly%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fconsumer-credit-card-debt-tops-1-trillion-first-time-ever-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%241%20trillion%20of%20such%20debt%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Fed%20data%20shows.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famericans-excess-savings-consumer-spending-us-economy-fed-study-2023-8%5C%22