e%20with%20documentation.%20The%20following%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20still%20remember%20when%20I%20was%20in%20kindergarten%20back%20in%20South%20Korea.%20I%20enjoyed%20playing%20Starcraft%2C%20a%20popular%20computer%20game%20at%20that%20time%2C%20and%20that's%20when%20my%20interest%20in%20computers%20and%20technology%20started.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20I%20grew%20older%2C%20I%20loved%20reading%20tech%20news%20articles%20about%20how%20tech%20is%20impacting%20lives.%20So%20in%20college%2C%20I%20set%20an%20end%20goal%20for%20myself%3A%20work%20in%20a%20strategy%20role%20at%20a%20tech%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20working%20at%20Google%2C%20I%20felt%20like%20I%20got%20a%20mini%20MBA.%20I'm%20grateful%20for%20all%20the%20lessons%20that%20my%20managers%20and%20my%20teams%20taught%20me%2C%20and%20I%20still%20use%20them%20to%20run%20my%20startup%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20certainly%2C%20my%20job%20at%20Google%20was%20stressful%3A%20we%20worked%20on%20a%20global%20team%20and%20some%20coworkers%20were%20based%20in%20Europe%20and%20Asia.%20So%20we%20had%20meetings%20at%205%20or%206%20a.m.%20on%20Tuesdays%20and%20at%2011%20p.m.%20every%20Wednesday.%20I%20felt%20I%20always%20had%20to%20give%20110%25%20every%20single%20day%20because%20my%20colleagues%20were%20extremely%20smart%20and%20hardworking.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHere's%20how%20much%20I%20made%20in%20each%20role%20at%20Google%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAnalyst%2C%20Trust%20and%20safety%20team%3Cbr%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cstrong%3EBase%20salary%3A%20%2470%2C000%2C%20Bonus%20target%3A%20%2410%2C500%20(15%25%20of%20base%20salary)%3Cbr%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cstrong%3ERelocation%20bonus%3A%20%247%2C500%2C%20Equity%3A%2060%20restricted%20stock%20units%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETotal%20compensation%3A%20%2488%2C000%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20joined%20Google's%20trust%20and%20safety%20team.%20We%20worked%20with%20engineers%20and%20sales%20teams%20to%20minimize%20abuse%20on%20the%20platform.%20By%20abuse%20I%20mean%2C%20for%20example%2C%20hackers%20who%20could%20get%20into%20your%20Google%20ads%20account%2C%20post%20random%20things%20on%20your%20behalf%20and%20spend%20money%20on%20your%20account.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20learned%20a%20lot%20of%20analytical%20skills.%20There%20was%20one%20project%20I%20worked%20on%20where%20we%20detected%20some%20suspicious%20activity%20on%20Google%20Ads%2C%20and%20I%20helped%20solve%20the%20issue%20with%20our%20engineers%20and%20our%20product%20managers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EStrategist%2C%20Trust%20and%20safety%20team%C2%A0%3Cbr%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cstrong%3EBase%20salary%3A%20%2474%2C506%20(%2435.82%2Fhour)%2C%20Annual%20bonus%3A%20%2411%2C175%3Cbr%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cstrong%3EEquity%3A%2060%20restricted%20stock%20units%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETotal%20compensation%3A%20%2485%2C681%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWithin%20eight%20months%20I%20was%20promoted%20to%20a%20strategist%2C%20where%20I%20was%20responsible%20for%20strategy%2C%20analytics%2C%20and%20operations%20for%20global%20Google%20Ads%20financial%20fraud.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20that%20point%2C%20I%20felt%20like%20I%20learned%20a%20lot%2C%20but%20didn't%20know%20if%20there%20was%20much%20else%20for%20me%20to%20learn.%20So%20I%20interviewed%20with%20different%20teams%20within%20Google.%20Then%2C%20about%20a%20year%20later%2C%20I%20successfully%20moved%20to%20the%20revenue%20strategy%20and%20operations%20team.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EStrategy%20and%20operations%20manager%2C%20Revenue%20strategy%20and%20operations%20team%C2%A0%3Cbr%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cstrong%3EBase%20salary%3A%20%24100%2C000%2C%20Annual%20bonus%3A%20%2418%2C500%3Cbr%3EEquity%3A%20%2430%2C000%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETotal%20compensation%3A%20%24148%2C500%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20team%20thinks%20about%20how%20to%20increase%20revenue%20for%20Google.%20We%20worked%20with%20the%20Google%20sales%20team%2C%20and%20I%20helped%20think%20about%20what%20markets%20we%20were%20going%20to%20tackle%20first%2C%20what%20incentives%20to%20set%20up%20for%20the%20sales%20team%2C%20and%20so%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESenior%20strategy%20and%20operations%20manager%2C%20Revenue%20strategy%20and%20operations%20team%3Cbr%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cstrong%3EBase%20salary%3A%20%24129%2C000%2C%20Annual%20bonus%3A%20%2422%2C500%3Cbr%3EEquity%3A%20%2446%2C500%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETotal%20compensation%3A%20%24198%2C000%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20year%20later%2C%20I%20was%20promoted%20again%20to%20senior%20strategy%20and%20operations%20manager.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20getting%20promoted%20frequently%20and%20I%20wanted%20to%20keep%20the%20momentum%20going%2C%20but%20at%20a%20certain%20point%2C%20I%20was%20told%20to%20wait%20my%20turn%20for%20a%20promotion%20%E2%80%94%20even%20though%20I%20was%20excelling%20in%20my%20role.%20That%20didn't%20sit%20well%20with%20me%20so%20I%20decided%20to%20leave%20Google.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EMy%20experience%20working%20in%20tech%20was%20determined%20by%20the%20team%2C%20not%20the%20company%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20a%20misconception%20that%20a%20big%20company%20has%20the%20same%2C%20uniform%20culture%20across%20teams.%20People%20often%20imagine%20Google%20is%20all%20about%20casually%20riding%20bikes%20around%20the%20campus%20and%20enjoying%20free%20food%20all%20day.%20But%20in%20reality%2C%20your%20experience%20is%20heavily%20shaped%20by%20the%20specific%20team%20you're%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20second%20team%20was%20full%20of%20former%20consultants%20%E2%80%94%20everyone%20put%20in%20maximum%20effort%20every%20single%20day%20and%20I%20felt%20like%20I%20had%20landed%20in%20a%20consulting%20firm.%20This%20culture%20shift%2C%20compared%20to%20my%20first%20team%2C%20made%20that%20time%20at%20Google%20a%20bit%20more%20challenging.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EIn%20hindsig