20and%20Hindu%20women%20exposed%E2%80%99%20was%20published%20in%20%3Cem%3EOrganiser%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20another%20news%20platform%2C%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Commune%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20in%20June.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Jyoti%20Singh%20directed%20both%20publications%20to%20remove%20the%20defamatory%20article%20from%20their%20platforms.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20takes%20years%20to%20build%20a%20reputation%2C%20and%20therefore%2C%20the%20right%20to%20reputation%20has%20been%20recognised%20as%20a%20fundamental%20right%20under%20Article%2021%20of%20the%20Constitution%2C%20the%20bench%20observed%2C%20per%20the%20news%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CNo%20doubt%2C%20Article%2019(1)(a)%20of%20the%20Constitution%20provides%20the%20right%20of%20freedom%20of%20speech%20and%20expression%20to%20all%20persons%2C%20however%2C%20it%20cannot%20be%20overlooked%20that%20the%20same%20is%20subject%20to%20restrictions%20under%20Article%2019(2)%20which%20includes%20defamation.%20The%20right%20to%20freedom%20of%20speech%20and%20expression%20cannot%20be%20taken%20as%20an%20unfettered%20right%20so%20as%20to%20defame%20and%20tarnish%20the%20reputation%20of%20another%20person.%20It%20has%20been%20repeatedly%20held%20by%20Courts%20that%20fundamental%20right%20to%20freedom%20of%20speech%20has%20to%20be%20counterbalanced%20with%20the%20right%20of%20reputation%20of%20an%20individual.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20high%20court%20said%20that%20prima%20facie%2C%3Cem%3E%20Organiser%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Commune%3C%2Fem%3E%20published%20the%20articles%20%E2%80%9Cin%20a%20reckless%20manner%20without%20any%20factual%20verification%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20the%20court%20said%20that%20the%20news%20coverage%20was%20harming%20the%20reputation%20of%20the%20school%20principal.%20The%20principal%20is%20a%20well-regarded%20individual%20within%20the%20country%20and%20has%20affiliations%20with%20multiple%20educational%20establishments%2C%20it%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20noted%20that%20the%20school%20principal%20has%20presented%20a%20strong%20case%20in%20his%20favour.%20The%20principal%20said%20that%20as%20long%20as%20these%20articles%20remain%20in%20the%20public%20domain%2C%20there%20is%20a%20high%20likelihood%20that%20they%20will%20keep%20causing%20harm%20to%20his%20reputation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20said%20that%20a%20police%20complaint%20has%20been%20filed%20against%20the%20two%20platforms%20and%20is%20pending%20inquiry.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EConsequently%2C%20the%20Court%20issued%20an%20ex%20parte%20ad-interim%20injunction%20against%20the%20two%20platforms.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20data-test-id%3D%5C%22text%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20order%20refrained%20from%20disclosing%20the%20identity%20of%20the%20plaintiff%20and%20the%20school%20he%20was%20associated%20with.%20This%20was%20done%20to%20uphold%20anonymity%20and%20safeguard%20their%20respective%20reputations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692346502000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F06%2F02121850%2Fdelhi-high-court-1558979556.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fhc-orders-organiser-to-take-down-article-accusing-christian-principal-of-exploiting-nuns-students%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22It%20takes%20years%20to%20build%20a%20reputation%2C%20and%20therefore%2C%20the%20right%20to%20reputation%20has%20been%20recognised%20as%20a%20fundamental%20right%20under%20Article%2021%20of%20the%20Constitution%2C%20said%20the%20high%20court.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A10%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fhc-orders-organiser-to-take-down-article-accusing-christian-principal-of-exploiting-nuns-students%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22NCLAT%20allows%20Go%20First%20lessor%20to%20conduct%