-sharma%2Farticleshow%2F102825565.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Can%20Children%20Out%20Of%20Wedlock%20Claim%20Ancestral%20Property%3F%20Verdict%20Reserved%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20today%20reserved%20its%20verdict%20on%20a%202011%20plea%20pertaining%20to%20the%20vexatious%20legal%20issue%20whether%20children%20out%20of%20wedlock%20were%20entitled%20to%20a%20share%20in%20the%20ancestral%20property%20of%20their%20parents%20under%20Hindu%20laws.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20bench%20comprising%20Chief%20Justice%20DY%20Chandrachud%20and%20justices%20JB%20Pardiwala%20and%20Manoj%20Misra%20heard%20submissions%20of%20several%20lawyers%20on%20a%20plea%20which%20is%20pending%20since%202011.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20will%20also%20decide%20the%20question%20whether%20the%20share%20of%20such%20children%20is%20limited%20only%20to%20the%20self-acquired%20property%20of%20their%20parents%20under%20Section%2016(3)%20of%20the%20Hindu%20Marriage%20Act.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20questions%20were%20referred%20to%20a%20larger%20bench%20by%20a%20two-judge%20bench%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20on%20March%2031%2C%202011.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20question%20which%20crops%20up%20in%20the%20facts%20of%20this%20case%20is%20whether%20illegitimate%20children%20are%20entitled%20to%20a%20share%20in%20the%20coparcenary%20(ancestral)%20property%20or%20whether%20their%20share%20is%20limited%20only%20to%20the%20self%20acquired%20property%20of%20their%20parents%20under%20Section%2016(3)%20of%20the%20Hindu%20Marriage%20Act%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20bench%20had%20said%20while%20referring%20the%20case%20to%20a%20larger%20bench.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20had%20said%20the%20provision%20makes%20it%20very%20clear%20that%20a%20child%20of%20a%20%26quot%3Bvoid%20or%20voidable%20marriage%26quot%3B%20can%20only%20claim%20rights%20to%20the%20property%20of%20his%20parents%2C%20and%20no%20one%20else.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20had%20disagreed%20with%20the%20earlier%20findings%20of%20the%20top%20court%20that%20such%20children%20will%20have%20no%20right%20in%20ancestral%20properties%20of%20their%20parents.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWith%20changing%20social%20norms%20of%20legitimacy%20in%20every%20society%2C%20including%20ours%2C%20what%20was%20illegitimate%20in%20the%20past%20may%20be%20legitimate%20today.%20The%20concept%20of%20legitimacy%20stems%20from%20social%20consensus%2C%20in%20the%20shaping%20of%20which%20various%20social%20groups%20play%20a%20vital%20role...%20in%20a%20changing%20society%20law%20cannot%20afford%20to%20remain%20static...%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20had%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Hindu%20law%2C%20in%20a%20void%20marriage%2C%20the%20parties%20do%20not%20have%20the%20status%20of%20husband%20and%20wife.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20the%20statute%2C%20husband%20and%20wife%20have%20the%20status%20in%20the%20voidable%20marriage.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20void%20marriage%2C%20no%20decree%20of%20nullity%20is%20required%20to%20annul%20the%20marriage.%20While%2C%20in%20a%20voidable%20marriage%20decree%20of%20nullity%20is%20required.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692344340000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2022-02%2Fa1ooga8_supreme-court-of-india_650x400_14_February_22.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fcan-children-out-of-wedlock-claim-ancestral-property-supreme-court-reserves-verdict-4307990%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Supreme%20Court%20today%20reserved%20its%20verdict%20on%20a%202011%20plea%20pertaining%20to%20the%20vexatious%20legal%20issue%20whether%20children%20out%20of%20wedlock%20were%20entitled%20to%20a%20share%20in%20the%20ancestral%20property%20of%20their%20paren