20and%20has%20been%20in%20constant%20touch%20with%20cinema%20in%20one%20way%20or%20the%20other.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fis-subhash-ghai-all-set-to-return-to-direction-with-the-khal-nayak-sequel-heres-what-the-filmmaker-has-to-say-%2Farticleshow%2F102824750.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22As%20UK%20Births%20Hit%2020-Year%20Low%2C%20Indian-Born%20Parents%20Take%20Record%20Share%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20number%20of%20babies%20born%20in%20England%20and%20Wales%20fell%20to%20its%20lowest%20level%20in%20two%20decades%20last%20year%2C%20while%20a%20record%20proportion%20came%20from%20parents%20who%20were%20both%20born%20abroad%2C%20highlighting%20a%20long-term%20shift%20in%20the%20nation's%20demographic%20makeup.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOf%20all%20live%20births%2C%2023.1%25%20were%20to%20non-UK-born%20parents%20-%20a%20proportion%20that%20has%20shot%20up%20from%2016.7%25%20in%202008%2C%20and%20is%20up%20from%2021.5%25%20a%20year%20ago%2C%20according%20to%20census%20data%20released%20Thursday%20by%20the%20Office%20for%20National%20Statistics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20figures%20also%20showed%20the%20share%20of%20babies%20born%20to%20British%20parents%20has%20slipped%2C%20from%2062%25%20to%2060.3%25%2C%20and%20the%20overall%20number%20of%20births%20sank%20to%20605%2C479.%20That's%20the%20lowest%20since%202002%2C%20and%20points%20toward%20slower%20population%20growth%20that%20could%20be%20a%20drag%20on%20both%20the%20economy%20and%20labor%20market%20in%20the%20decades%20ahead.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%26quot%3Bincrease%20in%20the%20number%20of%20non-UK%20born%20mothers%20is%20a%20good%20thing%26quot%3B%20given%20the%20UK's%20own%20falling%20birth%20rate%2C%20said%20Jonathan%20Portes%2C%20professor%20of%20economics%20and%20public%20policy%20at%20King's%20College%20London.%20But%20declining%20numbers%20of%20overall%20births%20is%20the%20%26quot%3Breal%20story%20here%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20it's%20a%20%26quot%3Bserious%20long-term%20social%20problem%20for%20us.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20rising%20number%20of%20births%20to%20foreign%20parents%20could%20help%20ease%20fears%20that%20the%20UK%20will%20face%20a%20labor%20supply%20crunch%20as%20its%20population%20ages%20and%20retirees%20out-pace%20the%20rate%20at%20which%20new%20workers%20come%20into%20jobs.%20But%20polling%20suggests%20migration%20is%20still%20an%20important%20concern%20for%20British%20voters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMore%20than%20half%20of%20the%20public%20favor%20a%20cut%20in%20immigration%2C%20according%20to%20a%20recent%20survey%20by%20Kantar%20and%20the%20Migration%20Observatory.%20That%20suggests%20rising%20numbers%20of%20births%20to%20migrant%20families%20could%20be%20a%20thorny%20issue%20for%20both%20major%20political%20parties%20as%20they%20face%20the%20prospect%20of%20a%20general%20election%20next%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENuni%20Jorgensen%2C%20a%20researcher%20at%20the%20Migration%20Observatory%2C%20pointed%20out%20that%20even%20while%20migrant%20parents%20were%20having%20more%20children%20than%20UK-born%20families%2C%20they%20still%20weren't%20having%20enough%20to%20replace%20the%20number%20of%20older%20people%20dropping%20out%20of%20the%20workforce.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo-called%20%26quot%3Breplacement-level%20fertility%2C%26quot%3B%20or%20the%20number%20of%20children%20each%20woman%20needs%20to%20have%20to%20replace%20the%20older%20generation%2C%20is%20currently%202.1%2C%20Jorgensen%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20can%20see%20that%20for%20both%20UK%20born%20and%20non-UK%20born%20women%2C%20fertility%20rates%20are%20below%20replacement%20level.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20number%20of%20children%20born%20to%20parents%20who%20were%20both%20from%20abroad%20hit%20139%2C953%20last%20year%2C%20up%20from%20134%2C308%20a%20year%20earlier%20and%20its%20highest%20level%20since%202017.%20Numbers%20have%20remained%20relatively%20flat%20for%20births%20involving%20one%20non-UK-born%20parent%2C%20while%20births%20to%20two%20UK-born%20parents%20have%20fallen%20to%20365%2C111%2C%20the%20lowest%20level%20in%20comparable%20data%20going%20back%20to%202008.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ONS%20data%20suggests%20fertility%20rates%20are%20falling.%20More%20women%20are%20choosing%20not%20to%20have%20children%20either%20for%20professional%20reasons%20or%20financial%20concerns%2C%20as%20the%20UK%20remains%20embroiled%20in%20a%20cost-of-living%20crisis.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20rise%20in%20the%20number%20of%20people%20immigrating%20to%20the%20UK%20in%20recent%20years%20is%20likely%20to%20have%20led%20to%20the%20jump%20in%20migrant%20parents%20in%202022.%20A%20record%20606%2C000%20more%20people%20moved%20to%20Britain%20than%20departed%20last%20year%2C%20boosted%20by%20humanitarian%20programs%20and%20demand%20for%20workers%20whose%20skills%20were%20in%20short%20supply.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20overtook%20Romania%20as%20the%20most%20common%20country%20of%20birth%20of%20foreign%20new%20mothers%2C%20after%20a%20third%20of%20all%20third%20of%20residence%20visas%20were%20granted%20to%20Indian%20nationals.%20Afghanistan%20also%20entered%20the%20top%2010%20for%20the%20first%20time%2C%20after%20the%20UK%20formally%20opened%20the%20Afghan%20Citizens%20Resettlement%20Scheme%20at%20the%20start%20of%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20also%20replaced%20Pakistan%20as%20the%20most%20common%20country%20of%20birth%20for%20non-UK-born%20new%20fathers.%20Pakistan%20had%20held%20the%20top%20spot%20since%20comparable%20data%20began%20in%202008.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20London%2C%20more%20than%20two%20thirds%20of%20births%20were%20to%20parents%20where%20at%20least%20one%20was%20from%20outside%20the%20UK.%20The%20highest%20percentages%20were%20seen%20in%20Brent%2C%20Westminster%2C%20Newham%20and%20Harrow%2C%20at%20more%20than%2080%25%20of%20births.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOutside%20of%20London%2C%20the%20Berkshire%20town%20of%20Slough%20and%20the%20Bedfordshire%20town%20of%20Luton%20were%20the%20areas%20with%20the%20highest%20rate%20of%20births%20to%20at%20least%20one%20migrant%20parent%2C%20at%2075%25%20and%2074.6%25%20respectively.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurther%20away%20from%20the%20capital%2C%20Oxford%20and%20Leicester%20saw%20the%20highest%20percentages%20at%2065.9%25%20and%2065%25%20respectively.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692340740000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2021-06%2Fit8dmhbo_baby-generic_625x300_09_June_21.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fas-uk-births-hit-20-year-low-indian-born-parents-take-record-share-4307905%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20number%20of%20babies%20born%20in%20England%20and%20Wales%20fell%20to%20its%20lowest%20level%20in%20two%20decades%20last%20year%2C%20while%20a%20record%20proportion%20came%20from%20parents%20who%20were%20both%20born%20abroad%2C%20highlighting%20a%20long-term%20shift%20in%20the%20nation's%20demographic%20makeup.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fas-uk-births-hit-20-year-low-indian-born-parents-take-record-share-4307905%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fas-uk-births-hit-20-year-low-indian-born-parents-take-record-share-4307905%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fas-uk-births-hit-20-year-low-indian-born-parents-take-record-share-4307905%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Anil%20'mistakenly'%20retweets%20post%20about%20OMG%202%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692340729000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.t