27.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'No%20further%20interest%20on%20penal%20charges'%3A%20RBI%20issues%20new%20guidelines%20for%20loans%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692331960000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2023-06%2F26%2Ffull%2F1687767723-2098.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Ffinance%2Fnews%2Fno-further-interest-on-penal-charges-rbi-issues-new-guidelines-for-loans-123081800156_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22RBI's%20new%20instructions%20on%20penal%20charges%20on%20loans%20shall%20come%20into%20effect%20from%20January%201%2C%202024%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A10%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Ffinance%2Fnews%2Fno-further-interest-on-penal-charges-rbi-issues-new-guidelines-for-loans-123081800156_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Health%20Ministry%20Obfuscates%20CAG%20Findings%20on%20Ayushman%20Bharat%20to%20Train%20Guns%20at%20Media%20Reports%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F09%2F29145422%2FScreen-Shot-2021-09-29-at-2.53.27-PM.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20In%20a%20rare%20instance%20of%20its%20kind%2C%20the%20Union%20health%20ministry%20issued%20a%20press%20release%20on%20August%2017%20attempting%20to%20fact-check%20media%20reports%20on%20the%20recent%20Comptroller%20and%20Auditor%20General%20(CAG)%20report%20on%20Ayushman%20Bharat%20that%20pointed%20to%20large-scale%20corruption%20in%20the%20scheme.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpib.gov.in%2FPressReleseDetail.aspx%3FPRID%3D1949844%5C%22%3Epress%20release%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20titled%20%E2%80%98Myths%20Vs%20Facts%3A%20Media%20Reports%20claiming%20AB%20PM-JAY%20beneficiaries%20who%20have%20been%20declared%20dead%20on%20the%20system%20availing%20treatment%20at%20hospitals%20are%20misleading%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20in%20the%20four-page%20press%20release%2C%20the%20ministry%20did%20not%20cite%20a%20single%20specific%20example%20wherein%20the%20media%20reports%20had%20erred%20in%20quoting%20the%20CAG%20report%20%3Cem%3Eper%20se%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20for%20instance%20to%20say%20the%20CAG%20report%20was%20misquoted%20or%20quoted%20out%20of%20context.%20All%20that%20the%20release%20did%20was%20to%20counter%20the%20shortcomings%20found%20in%20the%20CAG%20report%20without%20blaming%20the%20auditor.%20Instead%2C%20it%20put%20the%20onus%20on%20journalists%20for%20having%20quoted%20various%20parts%20of%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESample%20this%3A%20%E2%80%9CThere%20have%20been%20media%20reports%20claiming%20that%20the%20Comptroller%20and%20Auditor%20General%20of%20India%20(CAG)%20has%20flagged%20that%20treatments%20have%20been%20booked%20for%20AB%20PM-JAY%20beneficiaries%20who%20have%20been%20declared%20dead%20on%20the%20system.%20The%20reports%20further%20claim%20that%20the%20same%20beneficiary%20had%20been%20found%20to%20avail%20treatment%20across%20two%20hospitals%20at%20the%20same%20time.%20These%20media%20reports%20are%20completely%20misleading%20and%20ill-informed%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20ministry%E2%80%99s%20release%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20release%20goes%20on%20to%20qualify%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20hospitals%20are%20allowed%20to%20initiate%20request%20for%20pre-authorisation%20%5Bfor%20the%20purpose%20of%20availing%20claims%5D%20upto%20%3Cem%3Ethree%20days%20post%20the%20date%20of%20admission%20in%20the%20hospital%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%A6.In%20some%20cases%2C%20the%20patients%20got%20admitted%20and%20before%20their%20pre-authorisation%20was%20raised%2C%20they%20died%20during%20the%20treatment.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20words%2C%20the%20ministry%20said%20that%20patients%20might%20have%20died%20in%20the%20time%20period%20ranging%20%3Cem%3Efrom%20%3C%2Fem%3Edate%20of%20admission%20in%20the%20hospital%20%3Cem%3Eto%3C%2Fem%3E%20the%20date%20on%20which%20the%20pre-authorisation%20request%20was%20raised%20by%20the%20hospital%20concerned.%20And%20therefore%2C%20it%20was%20perfectly%20legitimate%20to%20pay%20a%20claim%20to%20the%20hospital%20even%20if%20the%20patient%20died%20during%20this%20period%20as%20the%20request%20might%20have%20been%20raised%20%3Cem%3Eafter%20%3C%2Fem%3Ethe%20admission%2C%20in%20a%20back-dated%20manner.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20did%20the%20CAG%20report%20really%20find%20a%20flaw%20with%20this%20process%3F%20It%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20seem%20so.%20The%20CAG%20report%20said%3A%20%E2%80%9D%20%5BThe%5D%20IT%20system%2C%20TMS%2C%20was%20allowing%20pre-authorisation%20requests%20of%20%5Bthe%5D%20%3Cem%3Esame%20%3C%2Fem%3Epatient%20who%20was%3Cem%3E%20earlier%3C%2Fem%3E%20shown%20as%20%E2%80%98died%E2%80%99%20during%20her%2Fhis%20earlier%20treatment%20availed%20under%20the%20scheme.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20a%20key%20difference%20between%20the%20ministry%E2%80%99s%20claim%20and%20the%20CAG%E2%80%99s%20report.%20The%20former%20said%20the%20pre-authorisation%20requests%20were%20raised%20by%20the%20hospitals%20%3Cem%3Eduring%3C%2Fem%3E%20an%20ongoing%20treatment.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%C2%A0%20the%20CAG%20report%20said%2C%20such%20requests%20were%20put%20up%20for%20the%20%3Cem%3Esame%3C%2Fem%3E%20people%20who%20were%20shown%20dead%20in%20the%20%3Cem%3Eearlier%20%3C%2Fem%3Etreatments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%2C%20the%20CAG%20report%20went%20on%20to%20add%3A%20%E2%80%9CData%20analysis%20of%20mortality%20cases%20in%20TMS%20%5BTransaction%20Management%20System%5D%20revealed%20that%2088%2C760%20patients%20died%20during%20treatment%20specified%20under%20the%20Scheme.%20A%20total%20of%202%2C14%2C923%20claims%20shown%20as%20paid%20in%20the%20system%2C%20related%20to%20%3Cem%3Efresh%20treatment%3C%2Fem%3E%20in%20respect%20of%20these%20patients.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20what%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fayushman-bharat-cag-report-pmjay-corruption%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20some%20other%20media%20publications%20too%2C%20had%20said%20in%20their%20articles.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThough%20now%20the%20ministry%20is%20finding%20fault%20in%20this%20reporting%2C%20the%20CAG%20report%20says%20that%20the%20National%20Health%20Authority%20(NHA)%20%E2%80%93%20the%20body%20that%20implements%20Ayushman%20Bharat%20Scheme%20at%20the%20Centre%20%E2%80%93%20had%20acknowledged%20this%20finding%20of%20the%20auditor.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CNHA%2C%20while%20acknowledging%20the%20audit%20comment%2C%20stated%20in%20July%202020%20that%20necessary%20check(s)%20have%20been%20put%20in%20place%20on%2022%20April%202020%20to%20ensure%20that%20PMJAY%20ID%20of%20any%20patient%20who%20has%20been%20shown%20as%20died%20in%20TMS%20is%20disabled%20for%20availing%20further%20benefit%20under%20the%20scheme.%E2%80%9D%20(PMJAY%20or%20Pradhan%20Mantri%20Jan%20Arogya%20Yojana%20is%20part%20of%20Ayushman%20Bharat%20Scheme%20under%20which%20the%20eligible%20families%20get%20Rs%205%20lakh%20insurance%20cover.)%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20despite%20the%20assurance%2C%20the%20CAG%20found%20that%20the%20gap%20continued%20to%20exist.%20%E2%80%9CAudit%20noted%20that%20patients%20earlier%20shown%20as%20%E2%80%98died%E2%80%99%20in%20TMS%20continued%20to%20avail%20treatment%20under%20the%20Scheme%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20CAG%20had%20said%20that%20not%20only%20were%20patients%20who%20had%20been%20shown%20dead%20earlier%20later%20registered%20for%20fresh%20pre-authorisation%20requests%2C%20but%20the%20system%20was%20so%20faulty%20that%20it%20allowed%20entering%20dates%20for%20%E2%80%9Call%20other%20entries%20such%20as%20admission%20date%2C%20surgery%20date%20and%20discharge%20dates%E2%80%9D%20for%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ministry%20gave%20another%20argument%20about%20the%20back-dated%20pre-authorisation.%20%E2%80%9CThere%20are%20also%20many%20instances%20where%20the%20patient%20is%20admitted%20in%20the%20hospital%20as%20a%20private%20patient%20(self-paid)%20but%20subsequently%20on%20discovering%20about%20the%20scheme%20and%20their%20eligibility%20under%20the%20scheme%2C%20the%20patient%20requests%20the%20hospital%20to%20register%20them%20under%20the%20scheme%20for%20free%20treatment.%20This%20feature%20to%20request%20for%20back-dated%20pre-authorisation%20helps%20in%20saving%20out-of-pocket%20expenditure%20of%20the%20beneficiaries.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ministry%20had%20given%20the%20same%20clarification%20to%20the%20CAG%2C%20as%20per%20the%20report.%20And%20the%20auditor%20termed%20it%20untenable.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20reply%20is%20not%20tenable%2C%20as%20pre-authorisation%20initiation%2C%20claim%20submission%20and%20final%20claim%20approval%20by%20Implementation%20Agency%2FState%20Health%20Authority%20for%20beneficiaries%20%3Cem%3Ealready%3C%2Fem%3E%20shown%20as%20dead%20during%20treatment%20earlier%2C%20indicate%20flaws%20in%20application%20and%20make%20it%20susceptible%20to%20misuse%20at%20user%20levels%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20CAG%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20release%20goes%20on%20to%20add%20that%20more%20than%2050%25%20of%20such%20cases%20were%20detected%20in%20public%20hospitals%2C%20which%20have%20no%20reason%20or%20incentive%20to%20commit%20fraud%20because%20the%20insurance%20claim%20would%20be%20deposited%20in%20these%20hospitals%20only.%20The%20CAG%20report%20made%20no%20such%20distinction.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20CAG%2C%20about%20Rs%207%20crore%20were%20paid%20to%20settle%20some%20such%20claims.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20456px)%2085vw%2C%20456px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F18090931%2FCAG-report-1.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22456%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F18090931%2FCAG-report-1.png%20456w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F18090931%2FCAG-report-1-286x300.png%20286w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-668529%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22479%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ESource%3A%20CAG%20report%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOne%20patient%2C%20many%20claims%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20charge%20that%20the%20ministry%20has%20tried%20to%20dispel%20is%20the%20CAG%20finding%20that%20one%20patient%20was%20shown%20to%20be%20availing%20treatment%20at%20different%20hospitals%20at%20one%20given%20point%20in%20time%20%E2%80%93%20thus%20indicating%20bogus%20patients%20were%20being%20treated.%20The%20CAG%20had%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CData%20analysis%20during%20desk%20audit%20(July%202020)%20revealed%20that%20the%20IT%20system%20(TMS)%20did%20not%20prevent%20any%20patient%20from%20getting%20admission%20in%20multiple%20hospitals%20during%20the%20%3Cem%3Esame%3C%2Fem%3E%20period%20of%20hospitalisations.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ministry%E2%80%99s%20release%20denied%20the%20charge.%20It%20said%20that%20a%20child%20under%20five%20years%20of%20age%20and%20a%20mother%20are%20registered%20under%20the%20same%20card.%20%E2%80%9CAccordingly%2C%20Ayushman%20Card%20can%20simultaneously%20be%20used%20for%20children%20and%20either%20of%20parents%20in%20two%20different%20hospitals%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%20The%20ministry%20went%20on%20to%20explain%20that%20if%20during%20delivery%2C%20a%20mother%20is%20treated%20at%20a%20hospital%20and%20the%20child%20requires%20neonatal%20care%20which%20is%20not%20present%20at%20that%20hospital%2C%20then%20the%20child%20would%20be%20shifted%20to%20another%20facility%20and%20would%20be%20registered%20under%20the%20same%20card.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ministry%20gave%20the%20same%20reply%20to%20the%20CAG%2C%20which%20the%20latter%20rejected.%20The%20CAG%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CContrary%20to%20the%20claim%20of%20NHA%2C%20these%20patients%20included%2023%2C670%20male%20patients.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20had%20another%20important%20finding%20on%20bogus%20claims.%20It%20found%20that%20the%20date%20of%20discharge%20for%20many%20patients%20for%20an%20%3Cem%3Eearlier%3C%2Fem%3E%20treatment%20was%20%3Cem%3Elater%3C%2Fem%3E%20than%20the%20date%20of%20admission%20for%20another%20treatment%20of%20the%20%3Cem%3Esame%20patient.%3C%2Fem%3E%20The%20CAG%20detected%20more%20than%2040%2C000%20such%20patients.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ministry%20nonetheless%20claimed%20that%20it%20has%20a%20%E2%80%9Cfour-step%20robust%20claim%20processing%20system%E2%80%9D%20and%20hospitals%20are%20penalised%20for%20such%20frauds%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMultiple%20IDs%20registered%20on%20one%20phone%20number%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20CAG%20finding%20which%20grabbed%20the%20maximum%20attention%20in%20media%20reports%20was%20the%20one%20in%20which%20it%20said%20that%20multiple%20beneficiaries%20were%20registered%20with%20the%20same%20mobile%20number.%20It%20said%207.5%20lakh%20beneficiaries%20were%20registered%20against%20the%20%E2%80%989999999999%E2%80%99%20mobile%20number%20and%20another%201.4%20lakh%20under%20the%20%E2%80%988888888888%E2%80%99%20number.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ministry%20said%20it%20was%20a%20useless%20finding%20as%20far%20as%20%E2%80%9Coperational%20and%20financial%20implications%20as%20beneficiary%20identification%20process%E2%80%9D%20are%20concerned.%20The%20first%20defence%20that%20the%20ministry%20gave%20was%20that%20the%20mobile%20numbers%20were%20registered%20only%20for%20the%20purposes%20of%20%E2%80%9Creaching%20out%20to%20beneficiaries%20in%20case%20of%20any%20need%E2%80%9D%20and%20for%20the%20%E2%80%9Cfeedback%E2%80%9D%20on%20treatment%20given%2C%20and%20not%20necessarily%20for%20the%20verification%20of%20beneficiaries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20ministry%20did%20not%20explain%20if%20the%20phone%20numbers%20were%20the%20same%20for%20so%20many%20people%2C%20how%20could%20the%20concerned%20officials%20reach%20out%20to%20so%20many%20different%20beneficiaries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ministry%20also%20said%20the%20government%20uses%20%E2%80%9CAadhaar%20based%20e-KYC%E2%80%9D%20for%20the%20verification%20purpose.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20details%20fetched%20from%20the%20Aadhar%20database%20are%20matched%20with%20the%20source%20database%20and%20accordingly%2C%20the%20request%20for%20Ayushman%20card%20is%20approved%20or%20rejected%20based%20on%20the%20beneficiary%20details%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20explained.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20is%20the%20Aadhaar-based%20verification%20fool-proof%3F%20The%20CAG%20could%20find%20violations%20against%20this%20too%2C%20at%20least%20in%20Tamil%20Nadu%2C%20wherein%20it%20discovered%204761%20registrations%20were%20made%20against%20seven%20Aadhaar%20numbers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ministry%20further%20added%20that%20many%20beneficiaries%20keep%20changing%20their%20mobile%20numbers%2C%20but%20how%20this%20fact%20has%20a%20bearing%20on%20the%20duplication%20of%20random%20phone%20numbers%20like%208888888888%20or%209999999999%20for%20so%20many%20beneficiaries%20is%20not%20clear.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ministry%20said%20that%20there%20is%20no%20room%20to%20deny%20treatment%20if%20the%20beneficiary%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20carry%20a%20valid%20mobile%20number%20and%20the%20mobile%20number%20inconsistency%20has%20no%20bearing%20on%20the%20scheme%20workflow.%20However%2C%20to%20the%20CAG%2C%20it%20had%20acknowledged%20this%20lacuna%2C%20and%20been%20quoted%20thus%20in%20its%20report%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%9CNHA%2C%20while%20agreeing%20with%20audit%20observation%2C%20stated%20(August%202022)%20that%20with%20the%20deployment%20of%20BIS%202.0%2C%20this%20issue%20shall%20be%20resolved.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOther%20findings%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ministry%E2%80%99s%20release%20dealt%20with%20three%20of%20the%20CAG%E2%80%99s%20findings.%20But%20on%20many%20others%2C%20the%20ministry%20has%20remained%20silent.%20Some%20of%20them%20are%20are%20as%20follows%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EIn%20as%20many%20as%202.25%20lakh%20cases%2C%20the%20date%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98surgery%E2%80%99%20done%20was%20shown%20to%20be%20later%20than%20the%20date%20of%20discharge%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EPayments%20transferred%20against%20such%20claims%20by%20hospitals%20which%20were%20dated%20even%20before%20the%20scheme%20was%20rolled%20out%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EPayments%20made%20to%20hospitals%20on%20dates%20that%20preceded%20submission%20of%20claims%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EBogus%20claims%20made%20for%20adults%20being%20treated%20under%20paediatric%20packages%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EHospitals%20empanelled%20under%20the%20scheme%20not%20fulfilling%20the%20mandatory%20criteria%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EEmpanelment%20of%20hospitals%20without%20physical%20verification%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EFailure%20of%20hospitals%20to%20provide%20services%20after%20empanelment%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EAfter%20empanelment%2C%20hospitals%20submitting%20only%200-5%20claims%2C%20indicating%20they%20were%20not%20providing%20services%20under%20the%20scheme%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EExcess%20payment%20amounting%20to%20Rs%2057.53%20crore%20were%20made%20to%20the%20empanelled%20hospitals%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EOne%20unique%20PMJAY%20ID%2C%20which%20is%20to%20be%20issued%20to%20each%20beneficiary%2C%20was%20found%20to%20registered%20against%20names%20of%20multiple%20beneficiaries%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EIneligible%20households%20registered%20as%20beneficiaries%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EBeneficiaries%20being%20charged%20for%20treatment%20when%20it%20is%20supposed%20to%20be%20totally%20free.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20matter%20of%20process%2C%20before%20the%20CAG%20report%20is%20finalised%20and%20tabled%20in%20the%20parliament%2C%20the%20auditor%20shares%20the%20findings%20with%20the%20department%2Fministry%20concerned%20to%20give%20it%20a%20chance%20to%20respond.%20The%20arguments%20given%20by%20the%20ministry%20in%20the%20August%2017%20press%20release%20were%20almost%20the%20same%20as%20to%20what%20it%20said%20to%20the%20CAG%2C%20as%20documented%20in%20the%20report.%20Despite%20the%20CAG%20rejecting%20them%2C%20they%20have%20been%20duplicated%20in%20the%20press%20release.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692330584000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F09%2F29145422%2FScreen-Shot-2021-09-29-at-2.53.27-PM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhealth%2Fhealth-ministry-obfuscates-cag-findings-on-ayushman-bharat-to-train-guns-at-media-reports%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20ministry's%20press%20release%20duplicates%20reasons%20and%20clarifications%20it%20had%20presented%20to%20the%20CAG%20%E2%80%93%20and%20the%20CAG%20had%20rejected.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhealth%2Fhealth-ministry-obfuscates-cag-findings-on-ayushman-bharat-to-train-guns-at-media-reports%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Ladakh%3A%20BJP%20Expels%20Veteran%20Muslim%20Leader%20Because%20His%20Son%20Eloped%20With%20a%20Buddhist%20Woman%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2F09125711%2Fvarun-nambiar-3SzqHcQ4eY0-unsplash.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESrinagar%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20Bharatiya%20Janta%20Party%20(BJP)%20in%20Ladakh%20has%20expelled%20a%2074-year-old%20Muslim%20leader%20from%20the%20party%20after%20his%20son%20eloped%20with%20a%20Buddhist%20woman.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20official%20handout%20issued%20on%20August%2016%2C%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20Ladakh%20unit%20said%20that%20Sheikh%20Nazir%20Ahmad%20has%20been%20expelled%20from%20primary%20membership%20of%20the%20party%20and%20relieved%20of%20his%20responsibilities%20as%20the%20state%20vice-president.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20party%20said%20the%20action%20was%20taken%20against%20him%20for%20his%20alleged%20involvement%20in%20his%20son%E2%80%99s%20elopement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CA%20meeting%2C%20chaired%20by%20the%20state%20president%20and%20attended%20by%20the%20executive%20members%2C%20was%20convened.%20Given%20ample%20time%20Sh.%20Nazir%20Ahmed%2C%20state%20vice%20president%20of%20BJP%20Ladakh%2C%20was%20provided%20an%20opportunity%20to%20clarify%20his%20involvement%20in%20a%20sensitive%20issue%20of%20the%20elopement%20of%20a%20Buddhist%20girl%20by%20his%20son%2C%20Manzoor%20Ahmed%2C%E2%80%9D%20reads%20the%20communique.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20BJP%20said%20the%20incident%20is%20deemed%20unacceptable%20by%20all%20religious%20communities%20in%20Ladakh%2C%20as%20%E2%80%9Cit%20jeopardises%20communal%20harmony%20and%20unity%20among%20the%20people%20of%20this%20region%E2%80%9D.%20%E2%80%9CAs%20a%20result%2C%20a%20decision%20has%20been%20reached%20to%20promptly%20relieve%20Sh.%20Nazir%20Ahmed%20of%20his%20responsibilities%20as%20state%20vice%20-president%20and%20revoke%20his%20primary%20membership%20within%20the%20BJP%20with%20immediate%20effect%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20party%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20BJP%20also%20wanted%20this%20action%20broadcast%20widely.%C2%A0The%20official%20handout%20about%20the%20expulsion%20is%20addressed%20to%20All%20India%20Radio%2F%20Doordarshan%20Leh%20%E2%80%9Cfor%20telecast%20in%20local%20news%20bulletin%E2%80%9D%2C%20apart%20from%20top%20leaders%20including%20Tarun%20Chugh%20(national%20general%20secretary)%2C%20Ashok%20Koul%20(general%20secretary%2C%20J%26amp%3BK%20%26amp%3B%20Ladakh)%20and%20Jamyang%20Namgyal%20(MP%20Ladakh).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETalking%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20over%20phone%2C%20Sheikh%20Nazir%20Ahmed%20said%20he%20has%20no%20role%20in%20the%20incident%20and%20there%20is%20no%20truth%20in%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20claims.%20%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20a%20baseless%20allegation.%20We%20are%20ourselves%20worried%20as%20we%20were%20planning%20to%20fix%20his%20nuptial%20knot%20with%20the%20daughter%20of%20my%20sister-in-law.%20My%20wife%20fainted%202-3%20times%20after%20he%20ran%20away%20from%20home%2C%E2%80%9D%20Ahmed%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20have%20been%20punished%20for%20a%20wrong%20committed%20by%20my%20son.%20What%20is%20my%20fault%3F%20When%20the%20children%20go%20against%20the%20wishes%20of%20their%20parents%2C%20do%20they%20tell%20their%20parents%3F%20They%20should%20have%20removed%20me%20for%20the%20post%20but%20not%20expelled%20me.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20the%20BJP%20leadership%20in%20Ladakh%20had%20asked%20him%20to%20trace%20his%20son.%20%E2%80%9CI%20told%20them%20that%20I%20am%20trying%20my%20best%20to%20find%20him%20but%20they%20told%20me%20to%20resign.%20I%20refused%20to%20resign%20and%20told%20them%2C%20%E2%80%98I%20am%20one%20of%20the%20founding%20members%20of%20BJP%20in%20Ladakh.%E2%80%99%20Those%20who%20expelled%20me%20are%20juniors%20to%20me%20in%20the%20party%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAhmed%20said%20they%20may%20have%20taken%20action%20against%20him%20as%20elections%20are%20near.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20that%20he%20was%20on%20Hajj%20pilgrimage%20when%20his%20son%20eloped%20with%20the%20woman.%20%E2%80%9CI%20was%20in%20Saudi%20Arabia%20when%20they%20ran%20away.%20I%20came%20to%20know%20about%20the%20incident%20when%20I%20returned%20from%20the%20Hajj%20pilgrimage%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOld%20association%20with%20the%20BJP%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAhmed%20said%20he%20has%20more%20than%20a%20decade-old%20association%20with%20the%20BJP%20in%20Ladakh.%20%E2%80%9CI%20am%20associated%20with%20the%20BJP%20right%20from%202010%2C%20when%20Rajnath%20Singh%20came%20here%20to%20announce%20the%20merger%20of%20the%20Ladakh%20Union%20Territory%20Front%20(LUTF)%20with%20BJP%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202002%2C%20different%20political%2C%20religious%20and%20social%20g