.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20parliamentary%20speeches%20were%20meant%20to%20defend%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20performance%2C%20so%20they%20had%20to%20be%20partisan%20but%20perhaps%20less%20combative.%20But%2C%20the%20tenor%20of%20the%20Independence%20Day%20speech%20ought%20to%20have%20been%20such%20as%20to%20fill%20the%20deepening%20chasm%20between%20the%20various%20sections%20of%20society%20and%20the%20political%20parties.%20To%20make%20India%20a%20developed%20country%20by%202047%2C%20to%20make%20India%20the%20third%20largest%20economy%20in%20the%20world%20in%20the%20next%20five%20years%2C%20and%20to%20make%20India%20great%20in%20the%20next%201%2C000%20years%20requires%20cooperation%20from%20all.%20None%20of%20these%20goals%20would%20be%20achieved%20if%20the%20present%20deep%20divides%20are%20not%20bridged.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F15153118%2FH20230815136672.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F15153118%2FH20230815136672.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F15153118%2FH20230815136672-300x154.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F15153118%2FH20230815136672-1024x525.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-668223%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22615%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EPrime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi.%20Photo%3A%20PIB%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ruling%20party%20has%20asserted%20that%20it%20has%20done%20well%20on%20all%20fronts.%20It%20has%20especially%20patted%20itself%20on%20the%20back%20for%20its%20economic%20management%20in%20spite%20of%20the%20Coronavirus%20pandemic%20and%20the%20Ukraine%20war.%20India%20is%20presented%20as%20the%20one%20bright%20spot%20in%20the%20gloomy%20world%20economic%20scenario%20and%20statements%20from%20the%20United%20Nations%2C%20International%20Monetary%20Funds%2C%20private%20banks%2C%20etc.%2C%20are%20cited%20to%20back%20its%20claim.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20reality%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOfficial%20data%20on%20growth%2C%20inflation%2C%20etc.%2C%20is%20presented%20to%20buttress%20the%20claims.%20But%2C%20officials%20holding%20high%20positions%20in%20the%20government%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fks-james-nfhs-modi-government-data-sets-iips%5C%22%3Eraised%20doubts%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%20the%20accuracy%20of%20data.%20Further%2C%20the%20ground%20reality%20is%20at%20variance%20from%20the%20rosy%20official%20depiction.%20The%20marginalised%20sections%2C%20especially%20women%2C%20and%20youth%20face%20massive%20unemployment.%20A%20large%20number%20of%20agriculturists%20complain%20of%20the%20non-viability%20of%20their%20profession.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20parliamentary%20speech%2C%20the%20ruling%20party%20contradicted%20itself%20on%20several%20counts.%20The%20Atmanirbhar%20package%20announced%20in%20May%202020%20to%20deal%20with%20the%20Coronavirus-induced%20crisis%20proposed%20the%20dismantling%20of%20the%20public%20sector%20through%20various%20forms%20of%20privatisation.%20It%20was%20proposed%20that%20there%20would%20not%20be%20more%20than%20one%20public%20sector%20unit%20(PSU)%20in%20any%20of%20the%20sectors.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Ftrillion-dollar-economy-india%5C%22%3EAverting%20a%20%2410-Trillion%20Dystopia%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%2C%20in%20the%20parliament%2C%20PSU%20banks%20were%20praised%20for%20announcing%20record%20profits%2C%20especially%2C%20the%20State%20Bank%20of%20India.%20Then%20why%20privatise%20them%20and%20lose%20the%20annual%20dividend%20that%20the%20government%20earns%20from%20them%3F%20The%20Life%20Insurance%20Corporation%20(LIC)%20also%20came%20in%20for%20praise%20while%20the%20insurance%20sector%20also%20sought%20to%20be%20privatised.%20Not%20only%20the%20PSU%20banks%20and%20insurance%20companies%20are%20profitable%2C%20but%20their%20social%20role%20in%20serving%20the%20poor%20is%20also%20critical.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHindustan%20Aeronautics%20Limited%20came%20in%20for%20praise.%20Then%2C%20why%20was%20it%20cut%20out%20of%20the%20Rafael%20deal%20in%20favour%20of%20a%20private%20company%20that%20had%20little%20experience%20in%20aircraft%20manufacture%3F%20This%20episode%20is%20a%20glaring%20example%20of%20the%20widespread%20prevalence%20of%20cronyism%20in%20India%2C%20which%20the%20prime%20minister%20says%20needs%20to%20be%20ended.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPersisting%20cronyism%20and%20corruption%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECronyism%20has%20been%20one%20of%20the%20major%20causes%20of%20rising%C2%A0non-performing%20assets%20(NPAs)%20among%20Indian%20banks.%20In%202015%2C%20the%20Reserve%20Bank%20of%20India%20(RBI)%20tightened%20its%20regulations%20which%20led%20to%20the%20double%20balance%20sheet%20problem%20%E2%80%93%20the%20balance%20sheets%20of%20the%20banks%20and%20businesses%20developed%20gaping%20holes.%20This%20impacted%20private%20investment%20and%20brought%20down%20the%20growth%20rate%20of%20the%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDid%20cronyism%20end%3F%20It%20has%20changed%20its%20form%20and%20reached%20new%20heights%20with%20conglomerates%20being%20favoured%20at%20the%20expense%20of%20others.%20Consider%20a%20few%20cases.%20Acquisition%20of%20Mumbai%20airport%2C%20allocation%20of%20smaller%20airports%2C%20ports%20and%20infrastructure%20projects%20to%20the%20favoured%20one%2C%20last-minute%20acquisition%20of%20ACC%20and%20Ambuja%20Cement%20by%20the%20favoured%20business%20and%20so%20on.%20The%20lesson%20for%20other%20businesses%20is%20that%20if%20they%20are%20highly%20profitable%20they%20could%20be%20grabbed%20by%20some%20other%20big%20businessman.%20The%20resulting%20damage%20to%20the%20business%20environment%20has%20led%20to%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livemint.com%2Fnews%2Findia%2Fhenley-report-2023-6-500-hnis-to-leave-india-uk-russia-to-attract-millionaires-wealth-to-grow-by-80-by-2031-11686653453424.html%5C%22%3Ehigh-networth%20Indians%3C%2Fa%3E%20(HNIs)%20leaving%20India%20since%202014%20and%20lakhs%20have%20given%20up%20Indian%20citizenship%20recently.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECronyism%20weakens%20economic%20administration%20and%20leads%20to%20the%20persistence%20of%20black%20income%20generation.%20A%20decline%20in%20the%20black%20economy%20would%20have%20led%20to%20India%E2%80%99s%20tax%2FGDP%20ratio%20to%20rise.%20It%20has%20remained%20at%20about%2016-17%25%20in%20the%20last%2010%20years.%20Direct%20taxes%20as%20a%20per%20cent%20of%20GDP%20has%20hovered%20at%20about%205.5-6%25.%20If%20the%20black%20economy%20had%20been%20checked%2C%20it%20should%20have%20conservatively%20risen%20to%2012%25%20of%20GDP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIncreased%20GST%20collections%20post-pandemic%20are%20being%20shown%20as%20an%20example%20of%20better%20compliance.%20But%20this%20is%20expected%20due%20to%20high%20inflation%2C%20increase%20in%20imports%2C%20and%20growth%20of%20the%20organised%20sector%20at%20the%20expense%20of%20the%20unorganised%20sector.%20A%20large%20number%20of%20fake%20companies%20to%20claim%20input%20credit%20are%20being%20detected%20every%20month%20and%20official%20evasion%20is%20running%20into%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20crores.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECorruption%20cases%20are%20persisting.%20During%20demonetisation%2C%20all%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbanking%2Fdemonetisation-99-of-scrapped-notes-came-back-into-system%5C%22%3Ehigh%20denomination%20notes%20came%20back%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20including%20the%20black%20money%20hoards%20of%20about%20Rs%203%20lakh%20crore.%20The%20government%20had%20promised%20to%20track%20this%20money%20and%20prosecute%20those%20who%20deposit%20their%20black%20funds%20into%20their%20bank%20accounts.%20Nothing%20of%20the%20sort%20has%20happened.%20The%20case%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fheroin-seuzure-adani-mundra-worry-indian-authorities%5C%22%3ERs%2030%2C000%20crore%20of%20drugs%20coming%20through%20Adani%20port%3C%2Fa%3E%20remains%20unresolved%20and%20only%20minor%20players%20were%20caught.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Findia-economy-performance-comparison-30-years%5C%22%3EHow%20Has%20the%20Indian%20Economy%20Done%20Vis-%C3%A0-vis%20Other%20Nations%20Over%20the%20Past%2030%20Years%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDaily%20new%20cases%20of%20corruption%20are%20exposed.%20Recently%20Comptroller%20and%20Auditor%20General%20(CAG)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livemint.com%2Fpolitics%2Fnews%2Fayushman-bharat-scheme-cag-report-exposes-dummy-numbers-aadhar-irregularities-11691998961683.html%5C%22%3Ehas%20flagged%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20lakhs%20of%20claimants%20are%20linked%20to%20the%20same%20mobile%20number%20under%20the%20Ayushman%20Bharat%20scheme.%20The%20CAG%20has%20also%20flagged%20inflating%20of%20road%20construction%20costs.%20Cases%20of%20fake%20Aadhar%20cards%20and%20other%20identities%20are%20being%20reported%20in%20the%20press.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EEconomy%20not%20yet%20the%20fifth%C2%A0largest%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndian%20economy%20is%20officially%20said%20to%20have%20become%20the%20fifth%20largest%20in%20the%20world%2C%20and%20now%2C%20it%20is%20being%20said%20that%20in%20the%20next%20five%20years%2C%20it%20will%20become%20the%20third%20largest.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20GDP%20data%20has%20huge%20errors.%20Since%202016-17%2C%20when%20demonetisation%20was%20announced%2C%20the%20unorganised%20sector%20has%20been%20on%20the%20decline.%20But%20the%20official%20data%20does%20not%20capture%20it.%20The%20organised%20sector%20is%20taken%20to%20be%20a%20proxy%20of%20the%20non-agriculture%20unorganised%20sector.%20So%2C%20a%20declining%20sector%20is%20represented%20by%20a%20rising%20sector.%20This%20results%20in%20an%20overestimation%20of%20the%20GDP%20and%20its%20growth%20rate.%20International%20agencies%20like%20the%20UN%2C%20IMF%20and%20private%20agencies%20are%20not%20data-gathering%20organisations%20and%20work%20with%20the%20official%20data%20and%20replicate%20the%20errors.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EConsequently%2C%20the%20economy%20instead%20of%20growing%20at%206-7%25%20per%20annum%20%E2%80%93%20as%20officially%20claimed%20%E2%80%93%20has%20been%20hardly%20growing%20since%202016-17.%20The%20huge%20error%20in%20the%20official%20data%20becomes%20apparent%20when%20the%202016-17%20growth%20rate%20is%20officially%20given%20as%208%25%20%E2%80%93%20the%20highest%20of%20the%20decade.%20But%2C%20reports%20from%20that%20time%20point%20to%20a%20decline%20in%20production%20and%20trade.%20With%20reasonable%20assumptions%2C%20it%20can%20be%20shown%20that%20growth%20was%20overstated%20by%20at%20least%205%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20this%20yardstick%20is%20used%20for%20the%20period%20subsequent%20to%202016-17%2C%20when%20GST%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbanking%2Findia-shadow-banking-system-fault-lines%5C%22%3ENBFC%20crisis%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20lockdown%20dragged%20the%20economy%20down%2C%20the%20economy%20has%20hardly%20been%20growing.%20So%2C%20presently%20India%20cannot%20be%20the%20fifth-largest%20economy.%20It%20is%20possibly%20the%20eighth%20or%20the%20ninth%20largest.%20Since%20the%20economy%20is%20still%20stagnating%2C%20it%20will%20not%20become%20the%20third%20largest%20in%20the%20next%20five%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInaccuracy%20in%20GDP%20data%20also%20means%20that%20consumption%20and%20investment%20data%20are%20incorrect.%20Further%2C%20if%20the%20unorganised%20sector%20is%20declining%20or%20even%20stagnant%20then%20poverty%20cannot%20be%20declining.%20The%20claim%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2F20-79-crore-indians-are-poor-urban-rural-divide-a-concern-niti-aayog%5C%22%3EMulti-dimensional%20poverty%3C%2Fa%3E%20(MDP)%20declined%20in%202020%20strains%20credibility.%20That%20was%20the%20pandemic%20year%20when%20health%20infrastructure%20was%20overwhelmed%2C%20a%20large%20number%20of%20deaths%20took%20place%20which%20were%20not%20recorded%20and%20schools%20were%20closed%20so%20that%20students%20could%20not%20attend%20class.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20the%20unorganised%20sector%20is%20the%20overwhelming%20employer%20in%20the%20economy%2C%20its%20decline%20underlies%20the%20growing%20unemployment%20problem%20with%20280%20million%20not%20having%20proper%20work%20and%20incomes.%20It%20is%20this%20that%20underlies%20family%20poverty.%20Inflation%20has%20added%20to%20the%20woes%20of%20the%20poor%20by%20reducing%20the%20purchasing%20power%20of%20their%20already%20low%20wages.%20This%20has%20caused%20demand%20to%20decline%20and%20resulted%20in%20an%20economic%20slowdown.%20At%20this%20rate%2C%20we%20do%20not%20know%20what%20will%20be%20the%20situation%20in%202027%20or%20a%20thousand%20years%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20social%20implications%20of%20unemployment%20and%20persisting%20family%20poverty%20are%20severe.%20It%20has%20led%20to%20frustration%20among%20the%20educated%20youth%2C%20resulting%20in%20growing%20substance%20abuse%2C%20rising%20violence%20in%20the%20family%20and%20crime.%20It%20has%20also%20resulted%20in%20lumpenisation%20and%20availability%20of%20semi-literate%20youth%20for%20nefarious%20purposes%20by%20vested%20interests.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20growth%20in%20the%20organised%20sectors%20at%20the%20expense%20of%20the%20unorganised%20sector%20has%20caused%20disparities%20to%20accentuate.%20So%2C%20GDP%20growth%20hardly%20represents%20the%20living%20standard%20of%20the%20marginalised%20sections.%20In%20any%20case%2C%20in%20per%20capita%20terms%2C%20the%20economy%20is%20at%20the%20138%3Cspan%3Eth%3C%2Fspan%3E%20position%20in%20the%20world.%20Being%20the%20fifth%20or%20the%20third%20largest%20world%20economy%20is%20no%20consolation%20to%20the%20marginalised.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20could%20also%20argue%20that%20if%20the%20marginalised%20were%20doing%20as%20well%20as%20officially%20portrayed%2C%20there%20would%20be%20no%20need%20for%20the%20government%20to%20give%20them%20free%20grains%20or%20gas%20cylinders%20or%20give%20Rs%206%2C000%20to%20the%20farmers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EConclusion%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20not%20to%20say%20that%20India%20has%20not%20made%20any%20gains%20on%20various%20fronts.%20More%20schools%2C%20hospitals%2C%20roads%2C%20trains%2C%20cars%2C%20white%20goods%2C%20etc%2C%20have%20come%20up%2C%20but%20these%20are%20a%20product%20of%20development%20over%20the%20last%2077%20years.%20The%20point%20being%20made%20here%20is%20that%20the%20macro-level%20claims%20have%20gaping%20holes%20papered%20over%20by%20faulty%20data.%20Further%2C%20there%20are%20contradictions%20in%20the%20official%20claims.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20it%20is%20claimed%20that%20there%20will%20be%20decolonisation%20of%20the%20mind.%20But%2C%20inviting%20foreign%20universities%20to%20set%20up%20campuses%20in%20India%C2%A0would%20only%20further%20colonise%20the%20mind%20since%20they%20will%20bring%20their%20framework%20and%20not%20promote%20an%20Indian%20ethos.%20The%20RBI%20and%20NITI%20Ayog%20invite%20foreign%20consultants%20for%20policy%20advice%20when%20it%20is%20known%20that%20these%20agencies%20suggest%20foreign%20expertise%20and%20purchasing%20from%20MNCs.%20Welcoming%20foreign%20direct%20investments%20(FDIs)%20undermine%20Indian%20firms%20that%20lack%20the%20technology%20to%20compete.%20It%20is%20an%20invitation%20to%20allow%20greater%20capture%20of%20our%20markets.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20claim%20of%20India%20being%20Vishwaguru%20sounds%20hollow%20when%20we%20increasingly%20depend%20on%20the%20import%20of%20technology.%20Dependence%20on%20FDI%2C%20remittances%2C%20foreign%20consultants%2C%20and%20audit%20firms%20is%20no%20sign%20of%20being%20Vishwaguru.%20US%20citizens%20are%20not%20clamouring%20to%20take%20up%20Indian%20citizenship%2C%20while%20a%20large%20number%20of%20Indians%20are%20leaving%20the%20country%2C%20including%20HNIs%2C%20to%20take%20up%20citizenship%20in%20the%20US%2C%20Australia%2C%20etc.%20We%20seek%20more%20H1B%20visas%20so%20that%20our%20talented%20resources%20can%20work%20in%20the%20US%20and%20often%20they%20settle%20down%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20brief%2C%20false%20self-praise%2C%20based%20on%20incorrect%20data%20and%20contradictory%20claims%2C%20only%20dents%20the%20credibility%20of%20the%20leaders.%20Even%20if%20the%20organised%20sectors%20have%20benefited%2C%20the%20reality%20is%20not%20hidden%20from%20the%20marginalised%20sections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EArun%20Kumar%20is%20the%20author%20of%3C%2Fem%3E%20Indian%20Economy%E2%80%99s%20Greatest%20Crisis%3A%20Impact%20of%20Coronavirus%20and%20the%20Road%20Ahead%3Ci%3E.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692322246000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F10%2F07131838%2Fmodi-sitha.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fthe-hollowness-of-modi-governments-tall-claims-and-self-praise-on-economy%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20BJP%20uses%20official%20data%20to%20buttress%20its%20tall%20claims%20on%20growth%2C%20inflation%20and%20other%20issues.%20But%20even%20those%20in%20the%20government%20have%20expressed%20doubts%20over%20the%20data.%20One%20cannot%20deny%20that%20the%20ground%20reality%20is%20at%20variance%20from%20the%20rosy%20depiction%20by%20the%20government.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A70%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fthe-hollowness-of-modi-governments-ta